adjectives.description: trafficable (comparative more trafficable, superlative most trafficable)

entries.meaning: Able to be trafficked or traded; marketable.
examples: Money itself is not only the price of all commodities in all civil nations, but it is also, in some cases, a trafficable commodity: the price whereof rises and falls, in several countries, upon occasion; and yieldeth either profit or loss

entries.meaning: Having good trafficability: of a vehicle, able to traverse terrain; of terrain, able to support vehicle movement.
